\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0 <$Scr_Ps::0>Here\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s how I\u8217\'92d rework this segment, focusing on the dynamics between Evan and Laura as he grapples with his moral doubts:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 The echoes of their laughter had barely faded when a wave of guilt washed over Evan. His smile faltered, a flicker of doubt clouding his eyes.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Laura,\u8221\'94 he began hesitantly, the words catching in his throat. \u8220\'93Are we sure we\u8217\'92re doing the right thing? This... it feels like we\u8217\'92re tricking Maggie.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Laura\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s expression hardened slightly, but her voice remained steady. \u8220\'93Is the scholarship legitimate?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes,\u8221\'94 Evan admitted, confusion mingling with his unease.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Did you set up a fair selection committee? Wasn\u8217\'92t that me?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes,\u8221\'94 he said again, the questions starting to feel like an interrogation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Did you make it available to everyone who qualified?\u8221\'94 Laura pressed on relentlessly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Evan nodded, a reluctant affirmation.}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0 Laura softened her tone, but her eyes remained fixed on his, unwavering in their resolve. }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Look, Evan, I get why you\u8217\'92re conflicted. You\u8217\'92re a good guy. But this is what\u8217\'92s best for Maggie, and sometimes...\u8221\'94 she hesitated, searching for the right words, \u8220\'93...sometimes a little deception is necessary for a greater good.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But what if we\u8217\'92re wrong?\u8221\'94 Evan asked, his voice barely above a whisper. \u8220\'93What if we could just tell her? Maybe it would be better that way.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Laura sighed, a hint of frustration in her voice. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Sure, if Maggie wasn\u8217\'92t so stubborn!\u8221\'94 She threw her hands up in exasperation. \u8220\'93We both know she\u8217\'92d refuse it if we were upfront, no matter how much we pleaded. This way, she accepts the scholarship, and maybe, down the line, we tell her the truth.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Evan remained silent, his brow furrowed in thought. Laura\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s words struck a chord, yet the guilt gnawed at him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I just\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 he started, then trailed off, unsure how to voice his lingering doubts.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Laura\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s expression softened as she reached out, squeezing his hand. \u8220\'93I know,\u8221\'94 she said quietly. \u8220\'93I have no doubts. Zero. Nada. It\u8217\'92s going to change her life. Sometimes we have to break the rules for the right reasons.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Evan\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mind flashed back to Guido\u8217\'92s recent advice, the words echoing in his head: \u8220\'93Feeling guilty isn\u8217\'92t doing anyone any good.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Laura was right. And so was Guido. This was about Maggie, not about his own conscience. There was no turning back now, and besides, Maggie\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s life was about to change for the better. He remembered Guido\u8217\'92s words, You\u8217\'92re either all in or all out. He\u8217\'92d been vacillating, but now it was time to be decisive.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Evan straightened his shoulders, a newfound determination chasing away the last vestiges of doubt. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Then what are we waiting for?\u8221\'94 he said, a genuine smile finally spreading across his face. \u8220\'93Let\u8217\'92s get moving. On to the finale!\u8221\'94}
